Use the standard library
This is how to order_by_points of nums:
  Remember that pairs is []
  Remember that i is 0
  Do this nums's length times:
    Remember that n is item i in nums
    Remember that text is tostring of abs of n
    Remember that points is 0
    Remember that j is 0
    Do this text's length times:
      Remember that ch is item j in text
      Increase points by toint of ch
      Increase j
    End do
    Add pairs to {"points": points, "value": n}
    Increase i
  End do

  Remember that result is []
  Do this pairs's length times:
    Remember that best_index is 0
    Remember that best is item 0 in pairs
    Remember that k is 1
    Do this diff of pairs's length and 1 times:
      Remember that current is item k in pairs
      When current is less than best, then:
        Remember that best is current
        Remember that best_index is k
      But, if not:
        When current is best, then:
          When current is less than best, then:
            Remember that best is current
            Remember that best_index is k
          End when
        End when
      End when
      Increase k
    End do
    Add result to best
    Remember that new_pairs is []
    Remember that m is 0
    Do this pairs's length times:
      When m is not best_index, then:
        Add new_pairs to item m in pairs
      End when
      Increase m
    End do
    Remember that pairs is new_pairs
  End do

  The answer is result
Now you know